<h2 id="research-advice-coordinator">Research advice coordinator</h2>

<p>Skill: general research skill &amp; project management.</p>

<p><strong>Jobs where the main responsibility is to synthesise the latest research knowledge in a given field, and give advice to the employer organisation about improving its services. One of the roles may be, a liaison between the research community and professional services, for example a charitable organisation working with clients.</strong></p>

<p>Potential work places:</p>

<ol>
  <li><a href="https://www.rnib.org.uk/who-we-are/jobs-rnib">RNIB research</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.guidedogs.org.uk/about-us/what-we-do/research">Guide Dogs Association research</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.mind.org.uk/about-us/our-policy-work/reports-and-guides/our-research/">MIND research</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.samaritans.org/about-samaritans/research-policy/">Samaritans research</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.leonardcheshire.org">Leonard Cheshire research</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.disabilityinnovation.com">GDI Hug</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://diversityandability.com">Diversity and Ability</a></li>
</ol>

<p>Networking nodes:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Maidstone or Brighton office of GDA.</li>
</ol>

